canonical:
  title: 送偰符寶還朝
  author: 河乙沚
  language: lzh
  text: 混一功成四海淸使星光彩照東瀛歸舟所載非他物秪是三韓上下情
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 送偰符寶還朝
  author: 河乙沚
  language: lzh
  text: 混一功成四海淸。使星光彩照東瀛。歸舟所載非他物。秪是三韓上下情。
korean:
  title: 송설부보환조
  author: 하을지
  language: kor
  text: |-
    통일의 공을 이루어 사해가 맑았거니
    사신 별의 광채가 동영을 비추누나
    돌아가는 배에 실은 것 다른 물건 아니네
    다만 이 삼한의 상하의 정일러라
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0240_010_1000&viewSync=OT
english:
  title: Sending Off Hyeok Bu, Keeper of the Seal, Returning to Court
  author: Ha Eul-ji
  language: eng
  text: |-
    The great work of unification complete, the four seas grow clear,
    The envoy's star shines bright, its radiance lighting the Eastern realm.
    The returning vessel carries no ordinary cargo—
    Only the deepest bonds between ruler and realm of Samhan.
  footnotes:
    - Samhan (三韓) refers to the three ancient Korean kingdoms, used here to represent Korea as a whole
    - The 'envoy's star' alludes to the diplomatic mission and the honor of the imperial messenger
    - The 'four seas' is a classical expression denoting all lands under heaven, here suggesting the unified Mongol-Yuan realm
